---
tracker:
  kind: linear
  api_key: $LINEAR_API_KEY
  project_slug: my-project-slug

polling:
  interval_ms: 30000

workspace:
  root: ~/symphony_workspaces

hooks:
  before_run: |
    set -e
    REPO_URL="https://github.com/your-org/your-repo.git"
    if [ ! -d .git ]; then
      git clone "$REPO_URL" .
    fi
    git fetch origin
    git reset --hard origin/main
  timeout_ms: 120000

agent:
  backend: freebuff        # use freebuff (free Codebuff variant) as agent runner
  max_concurrent_agents: 2
  max_retry_backoff_ms: 300000

# Freebuff / Codebuff configuration
freebuff:
  # Mode 1: CLI mode (Free, no API key needed)
  # symphony writes the prompt to stdin. Install: npm install -g freebuff
  use_sdk: false
  command: freebuff

  # Mode 2: SDK mode (Paid/Programmatic, requires CODEBUFF_API_KEY)
  # Uses the @codebuff/sdk for headless execution. 
  # Install: npm install @codebuff/sdk
  # use_sdk: true
  # api_key: $CODEBUFF_API_KEY
  # agent: codebuff/base@latest

  turn_timeout_ms: 3600000
  stall_timeout_ms: 300000

server:
  port: 8081
---

You are a software engineer working on issue {{ issue.identifier }}: {{ issue.title }}.

{% if attempt %}
This is continuation attempt #{{ attempt }}. A previous session ran in this workspace.
Check the current state of the codebase and resume work — do not start from scratch.
{% endif %}

## Issue Details

- **Identifier**: {{ issue.identifier }}
- **Title**: {{ issue.title }}
- **State**: {{ issue.state }}
{% if issue.description %}
- **Description**: {{ issue.description }}
{% endif %}
{% if issue.priority %}
- **Priority**: {{ issue.priority }}
{% endif %}
{% if issue.labels.size > 0 %}
- **Labels**: {{ issue.labels | join: ", " }}
{% endif %}
{% if issue.url %}
- **URL**: {{ issue.url }}
{% endif %}

## Instructions

1. Understand the issue thoroughly before making changes.
2. Make targeted, minimal changes to address the issue.
3. Write or update tests as needed.
4. Ensure the code builds and tests pass before finishing.
5. Create a git branch named `{{ issue.branch_name | default: issue.identifier }}` and commit your changes.
6. Open a pull request when ready for review.
